headline: Principal Financial's profit rises on higher premiums, fee income
summary: Insurer Principal Financial Group reported a rise in first-quarter profit on Thursday, helped by higher premiums and fee income. The Trump administration's back-and-forth on tariffs has driven up macroeconomic uncertainty and market volatility, boosting demand for insurance products as risk management becomes more essential. Asset managers also benefit from market turbulence as investors scramble to actively adjust their portfolios.

headline: Principal Financial: Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) — Principal Financial Group Inc. PFG) on Thursday reported first-quarter net income of $48.1 million. The Des Moines, Iowa-based company said it had net income of 21 cents per share.
